{
  "text": "Chloride in soil increased after contamination and decreased significantly below the background levels at the end of the study. There is the likelihood that the passage of contaminated soil across the gut of earthworms may have influenced the alteration of chloride leading to the decreased. Also, the activity of the earthworm's calciferous glands [CITATION_1] ) may have altered the levels of chloride in favour of the bioremediation process.",
